summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2016 HOLIDAY RAMBLER VACATIONER. ON MORE THAN ONE OCCASION, THE CONTACT REPORTED TO THE DEALER THAT THERE WAS AN ABNORMAL NOISE WHEN THE MOTOR HOME WAS IN MOTION. IN ADDITION, WHILE THE VEHICLE WAS BEING DRIVEN, THE DASHBOARD MOVED AND THERE WAS A CRACK NEAR THE TRIM AND WINDSHIELD. THE CONTACT HAD TO PARK THE MOTOR HOME DUE TO THE FAILURE. THE VEHICLE WAS LATER TAKEN TO A DEALER AND RECOMMENDED A THIRD PARTY SOURCE. THE CONTACT LATER RECEIVED NOTIFICATION OF NHTSA CAMPAIGN NUMBER: 16V784000 (SERVICE BRAKES, HYDRAULIC, ELECTRICAL SYSTEM), BUT HAD ALREADY EXPERIENCED THE FAILURE. THE VIN WAS NOT AVAILABLE. THE APPROXIMATE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 6,000. PARTS DISTRIBUTION DISCONNECT.
